QUIZ
1. can redeclare var but cannot redeclare let. var has function scope, let has block scope
2. can reassign and redeclare var, but can't do either with const. const has block scope, var has function scope
3. can reassign with let, but not with const.
4. hoisting means vars are "hoisted" to the top of the code and compiled before the declaration of the vars.
